00:00:15.932 --> 00:00:17.475 position:50% align:center
[HONOKA gasps]
We did it!

00:00:17.559 --> 00:00:20.478 position:50% align:center
The results are just
as expected, huh?

00:00:20.562 --> 00:00:22.564 position:50% align:center
[HONOKA]
Congratulations, Miyuki!

00:00:22.647 --> 00:00:23.898 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI]
It's so wonderful!

00:00:23.982 --> 00:00:26.317 position:50% align:center
They put my brother's
name right next to mine!

00:00:26.401 --> 00:00:28.111 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI giggles]

00:00:28.194 --> 00:00:29.988 position:50% align:center
I can't decide if that
attachment you have

00:00:30.071 --> 00:00:31.614 position:50% align:center
for your brother is
disappointing--

00:00:31.698 --> 00:00:34.576 position:50% align:center
Or if it's cute and endearing!

00:00:34.659 --> 00:00:36.578 position:50% align:center
Either way! These scores
should get us into

00:00:36.661 --> 00:00:39.289 position:50% align:center
the Nine Schools
Competition! Nice work!

00:00:39.372 --> 00:00:43.877 position:50% align:center
[SHIZUKU grunts] Thanks; crammed
like crazy to be extra sure.

00:00:43.960 --> 00:00:46.004 position:50% align:center
They had better choose me.

00:00:46.087 --> 00:00:49.466 position:50% align:center
Uh, why is Shizuku
on fire? Is she okay?

00:00:49.549 --> 00:00:51.134 position:50% align:center
Yeah, the Nine
Schools Competition

00:00:51.217 --> 00:00:53.845 position:50% align:center
has a habit of sending
Shizuku into beast mode.

00:00:53.928 --> 00:00:56.181 position:50% align:center
Every year, she goes
by herself to watch it.

00:00:56.264 --> 00:00:57.599 position:50% align:center
She likes to try
and gather intel

00:00:57.682 --> 00:00:59.309 position:50% align:center
on all of the frontrunners.

00:00:59.392 --> 00:01:00.685 position:50% align:center
Oh, my!

00:01:00.769 --> 00:01:01.978 position:50% align:center
So, this would be your first
year as a contestant,

00:01:02.062 --> 00:01:03.855 position:50% align:center
rather than a spectator!

00:01:03.938 --> 00:01:06.775 position:50% align:center
[SHIZUKU]
Mm. If I qualify, yeah.

00:01:08.568 --> 00:01:10.070 position:50% align:center
[MAYUMI] There's been
no official announcement yet

00:01:10.153 --> 00:01:11.446 position:50% align:center
on our school's lineup...

00:01:11.529 --> 00:01:12.572 position:50% align:center
But this year's rookie group

00:01:12.655 --> 00:01:14.741 position:50% align:center
is shaping up to
be quite stellar.

00:01:14.824 --> 00:01:17.285 position:50% align:center
And I think it's safe to say
that Mitsui and Kitayama

00:01:17.369 --> 00:01:19.162 position:50% align:center
will be in there with you.

00:01:20.246 --> 00:01:21.831 position:50% align:center
[MAYUMI]
The National Magic High School

00:01:21.915 --> 00:01:24.084 position:50% align:center
Goodwill Tournament
of Magic Skills.

00:01:24.167 --> 00:01:26.795 position:50% align:center
Or the Nine Schools Competition.

00:01:26.878 --> 00:01:28.672 position:50% align:center
It's held once every year.

00:01:28.755 --> 00:01:31.174 position:50% align:center
The top-ranking students
from every magic high school

00:01:31.257 --> 00:01:34.177 position:50% align:center
come together to
compete for glory.

00:01:34.260 --> 00:01:35.970 position:50% align:center
You're an invaluable
asset to our team,

00:01:36.054 --> 00:01:38.723 position:50% align:center
so I'm expecting great things
from you out there.

00:01:38.807 --> 00:01:40.225 position:50% align:center
Can I count on you?

00:01:40.308 --> 00:01:41.726 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI]
Yes!

00:03:19.282 --> 00:03:21.201 position:50% align:center
[TATSUYA]
I'm Shiba from Class 1-E.

00:03:21.284 --> 00:03:22.619 position:50% align:center
During the Competition,

00:03:22.702 --> 00:03:25.121 position:50% align:center
I'll be calibrating your CADs,
putting together your

00:03:25.205 --> 00:03:29.084 position:50% align:center
training regimens, and
formulating strategies with you.

00:03:29.167 --> 00:03:30.794 position:50% align:center
[AZUSA] As a member
of the technical staff,

00:03:30.877 --> 00:03:32.545 position:50% align:center
Mr. Shiba's here to support you!

00:03:32.629 --> 00:03:36.466 position:50% align:center
Go ahead and ask him anything
you want! Don't hold back!

00:03:36.549 --> 00:03:38.802 position:50% align:center
[NANAMI]
So we're getting a guy, then?

00:03:38.885 --> 00:03:42.180 position:50% align:center
Honestly, I would prefer it
if we had a female engineer.

00:03:42.263 --> 00:03:43.890 position:50% align:center
Kazumi...

00:03:43.973 --> 00:03:46.101 position:50% align:center
[AZUSA]
Uh, I know. It's just that...

00:03:46.184 --> 00:03:48.645 position:50% align:center
I get it. I thought that
would have been better myself,

00:03:48.728 --> 00:03:50.772 position:50% align:center
but the thing is...

00:03:50.855 --> 00:03:55.276 position:50% align:center
We don't want you or any other
Course Two for that matter.

00:03:55.360 --> 00:03:58.279 position:50% align:center
The guys... have
already made it very clear

00:03:58.363 --> 00:03:59.572 position:50% align:center
that they don't want me.

00:03:59.656 --> 00:04:02.534 position:50% align:center
Seriously, how stupid
can those guys be?

00:04:02.617 --> 00:04:03.660 position:50% align:center
You'd think the
test scores would

00:04:03.743 --> 00:04:05.912 position:50% align:center
have made some kinda difference.

00:04:05.995 --> 00:04:08.456 position:50% align:center
He's a Course Two student who's
been assigned to the tech staff;

00:04:08.540 --> 00:04:11.167 position:50% align:center
that's already
unprecedented as it is.

00:04:11.251 --> 00:04:12.836 position:50% align:center
That should serve
as more than enough proof

00:04:12.919 --> 00:04:15.171 position:50% align:center
that Tatsuya is capable
of supporting us.

00:04:15.255 --> 00:04:18.133 position:50% align:center
[HONOKA] Right! Miyuki's
brother is incredibly talented!

00:04:18.216 --> 00:04:20.176 position:50% align:center
Which means we should
feel lucky to have him!

00:04:20.260 --> 00:04:21.177 position:50% align:center
You know?

00:04:21.261 --> 00:04:22.637 position:50% align:center
That's right.

00:04:22.721 --> 00:04:24.889 position:50% align:center
[SUBARU] Whether you're in
Course Two, or you're a guy,

00:04:24.973 --> 00:04:26.349 position:50% align:center
long as you're good at your job,

00:04:26.433 --> 00:04:28.476 position:50% align:center
I don't see what
there's to complain about.

00:04:28.560 --> 00:04:30.895 position:50% align:center
I guess, if you say so, Subaru.

00:04:30.979 --> 00:04:33.064 position:50% align:center
Well, excited to work with you!

00:04:33.148 --> 00:04:35.984 position:50% align:center
Hey, Tatsuya, I have a
question regarding the magic

00:04:36.067 --> 00:04:37.902 position:50% align:center
I'll be using in the
Ice Pillars Break match.

00:04:37.986 --> 00:04:40.071 position:50% align:center
Hey! No fair, Shizuku!

00:04:40.155 --> 00:04:42.741 position:50% align:center
Hey! Do y'think you'd
be able to adjust my CAD?

00:04:42.824 --> 00:04:44.075 position:50% align:center
Yeah! Mine, too!

00:04:44.159 --> 00:04:46.494 position:50% align:center
[GROUP chatters]

00:04:50.040 --> 00:04:52.083 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI]
Hmm. You know, Brother,

00:04:52.167 --> 00:04:55.211 position:50% align:center
you seemed to be enjoying
yourself a lot this afternoon.

00:04:55.295 --> 00:04:57.505 position:50% align:center
[TATSUYA]
Did I? I'll admit

00:04:57.589 --> 00:04:59.382 position:50% align:center
talking to the brilliant
magicians chosen for

00:04:59.466 --> 00:05:02.427 position:50% align:center
the Nine Schools Competition was
more than a little intriguing.

00:05:02.510 --> 00:05:06.139 position:50% align:center
[gasps] I knew it!

00:05:06.222 --> 00:05:09.142 position:50% align:center
Honoka, Shizuku, Eimi,
Subaru, and the others--

00:05:09.225 --> 00:05:11.186 position:50% align:center
they're all so sweet
and lovely, aren't they?

00:05:11.269 --> 00:05:12.562 position:50% align:center
Uh?

00:05:12.645 --> 00:05:15.357 position:50% align:center
Uh... Hey, what's this about?

00:05:15.440 --> 00:05:17.567 position:50% align:center
I think that you might have
misunderstood me.

00:05:17.650 --> 00:05:19.027 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI]
Having lecherous thoughts

00:05:19.110 --> 00:05:21.112 position:50% align:center
about my classmates, are we?
Well, I'm afraid, Brother,

00:05:21.196 --> 00:05:23.531 position:50% align:center
you've left me with no choice.

00:05:24.783 --> 00:05:26.993 position:50% align:center
This is your punishment!

00:05:29.913 --> 00:05:32.040 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI]
The Self-Restoration Sequence.

00:05:32.123 --> 00:05:34.751 position:50% align:center
When triggered, it reads
the Eidos from a backup

00:05:34.834 --> 00:05:36.294 position:50% align:center
and restores it.

00:05:36.378 --> 00:05:39.339 position:50% align:center
This is my brother's
unique ability.

00:05:39.422 --> 00:05:41.466 position:50% align:center
So I guess... in a way

00:05:41.549 --> 00:05:44.177 position:50% align:center
this is kind of like
sibling roughhousing.

00:05:44.260 --> 00:05:47.013 position:50% align:center
After all, no matter
how brutal the attack,

00:05:47.097 --> 00:05:48.932 position:50% align:center
no matter how
grievous the injury,

00:05:49.015 --> 00:05:51.685 position:50% align:center
no one can ever
hurt my brother.

00:05:56.272 --> 00:05:57.857 position:50% align:center
Please forgive me, Brother.

00:05:57.941 --> 00:06:00.276 position:50% align:center
I went a little too
far with my prank.

00:06:00.360 --> 00:06:03.405 position:50% align:center
[TATSUYA]
Hm. That wasn't very nice.

00:06:24.467 --> 00:06:25.635 position:50% align:center
[STUDENT 06A]
Look!

00:06:25.719 --> 00:06:27.387 position:50% align:center
It's the team favored
to win the competition!

00:06:27.470 --> 00:06:29.305 position:50% align:center
Third High School!

00:06:29.389 --> 00:06:30.473 position:50% align:center
[STUDENT 06B]
Hey! Isn't that

00:06:30.557 --> 00:06:32.392 position:50% align:center
the Crimson Prince
of the Ichijo Family?

00:06:32.475 --> 00:06:34.185 position:50% align:center
One of the Ten Master Clans!

00:06:34.269 --> 00:06:35.353 position:50% align:center
[STUDENT 06C]
You're right!

00:06:35.437 --> 00:06:37.022 position:50% align:center
And that's Cardinal
George next to him!

00:06:37.105 --> 00:06:39.816 position:50% align:center
They're Third High
School's golden combo!

00:06:40.817 --> 00:06:42.402 position:50% align:center
[AIRI]
You have got to be kidding...

00:06:42.485 --> 00:06:44.529 position:50% align:center
Can you believe how carelessly
the boys are behaving

00:06:44.612 --> 00:06:46.281 position:50% align:center
on the eve of battle?

00:06:46.364 --> 00:06:47.699 position:50% align:center
From the way
they're carrying on,

00:06:47.782 --> 00:06:50.410 position:50% align:center
you'd think this was some
kind of social gathering.

00:06:50.493 --> 00:06:52.037 position:50% align:center
Just goes to show
how many people

00:06:52.120 --> 00:06:53.747 position:50% align:center
fail to take
this thing seriously.

00:06:53.830 --> 00:06:56.750 position:50% align:center
Calling it right now--Third
High's got this in the bag.

00:06:56.833 --> 00:06:58.918 position:50% align:center
You're being a little
too cavalier yourself,

00:06:59.002 --> 00:07:00.754 position:50% align:center
don't you think, Toko?

00:07:00.837 --> 00:07:01.880 position:50% align:center
[STUDENTS gasp]

00:07:01.963 --> 00:07:03.506 position:50% align:center
[TOKO]
Huh?

00:07:06.301 --> 00:07:07.969 position:50% align:center
[STUDENTS murmur]

00:07:08.053 --> 00:07:09.637 position:50% align:center
[SHIORI]
So that's First High School.

00:07:09.721 --> 00:07:12.515 position:50% align:center
They're hoping for their third
straight victory, I'm sure.

00:07:12.599 --> 00:07:13.892 position:50% align:center
Y'know what I heard, earlier?

00:07:13.975 --> 00:07:16.311 position:50% align:center
They got into a traffic
accident on their way here.

00:07:16.394 --> 00:07:18.104 position:50% align:center
Looks like they're
all right, though.

00:07:18.188 --> 00:07:19.481 position:50% align:center
I'm glad they are.

00:07:19.564 --> 00:07:21.733 position:50% align:center
There's no better way
to prove our abilities

00:07:21.816 --> 00:07:24.361 position:50% align:center
than by defeating our opponents
when they're in peak condition.

00:07:24.444 --> 00:07:26.196 position:50% align:center
[Ichijo Fan Club 06A]
M-Mr. Ichijo?

00:07:26.279 --> 00:07:28.490 position:50% align:center
Is there something the matter?

00:07:30.992 --> 00:07:32.869 position:50% align:center
She's beautiful...

00:07:32.952 --> 00:07:35.080 position:50% align:center
Hey, Ichijo.

00:07:35.163 --> 00:07:37.791 position:50% align:center
What has him so
mesmerized? I wonder...

00:07:37.874 --> 00:07:39.459 position:50% align:center
[AIRI gasps]

00:07:49.260 --> 00:07:50.929 position:50% align:center
Just who is that girl?

00:07:51.012 --> 00:07:52.180 position:50% align:center
It's easy to understand why

00:07:52.263 --> 00:07:54.057 position:50% align:center
Ichijo would be
so taken with her.

00:07:54.140 --> 00:07:56.685 position:50% align:center
No kidding. I almost had
a heart attack myself.

00:07:56.768 --> 00:07:57.811 position:50% align:center
[AIRI scoffs]

00:07:59.437 --> 00:08:00.730 position:50% align:center
[AIRI]
If I had to guess,

00:08:00.814 --> 00:08:02.774 position:50% align:center
I'd say you're from an
illustrious family, aren't you?

00:08:02.857 --> 00:08:04.526 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:08:04.609 --> 00:08:05.652 position:50% align:center
[AIRI]
Nice to meet you.

00:08:05.735 --> 00:08:08.530 position:50% align:center
I'm Airi Isshiki.
I attend Third High.

00:08:08.613 --> 00:08:13.118 position:50% align:center
As does Shiori Kanou here
and Toko Tsukushiin.

00:08:13.201 --> 00:08:17.080 position:50% align:center
Very nice to meet the three
of you! I'm Miyuki Shiba.

00:08:17.163 --> 00:08:18.373 position:50% align:center
"Shiba"?

00:08:18.456 --> 00:08:20.709 position:50% align:center
[AIRI] I don't recognize
that name at all.

00:08:20.792 --> 00:08:22.002 position:50% align:center
[THIRD HIGH GIRL 06A]
Looks like things are finally

00:08:22.085 --> 00:08:23.753 position:50% align:center
getting interesting,
huh, Ms. Mizuo?

00:08:23.837 --> 00:08:26.589 position:50% align:center
Are you having fun watching
all the First Years square off?

00:08:26.673 --> 00:08:27.882 position:50% align:center
Yes!

00:08:27.966 --> 00:08:30.051 position:50% align:center
Part of the fun of the
Nine Schools Competition!

00:08:30.135 --> 00:08:31.803 position:50% align:center
Though, when I started,

00:08:31.886 --> 00:08:34.264 position:50% align:center
First High was so
overwhelmingly strong.

00:08:34.347 --> 00:08:38.018 position:50% align:center
We were far too intimidated by
them to go up and say hello.

00:08:38.101 --> 00:08:40.061 position:50% align:center
[HONOKA]
I can't believe her!

00:08:40.145 --> 00:08:41.938 position:50% align:center
[HONOKA growls]
That's so rude!

00:08:42.022 --> 00:08:43.773 position:50% align:center
What's that girl's problem?!

00:08:43.857 --> 00:08:44.941 position:50% align:center
[AIRI]
I'm sorry, you mean to tell me

00:08:45.025 --> 00:08:47.819 position:50% align:center
you're just a member
of the underclass?

00:08:47.902 --> 00:08:49.571 position:50% align:center
